msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p> 
#. VAR: Ovādavagga → nāvābhirū­hana­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 28"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "28. Nāvābhiruhanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on boarding boats"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.28.1"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.292"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="609"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

#. VAR: ekaṃ nāvaṃ → ekanāvaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya "
"ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhanti."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of six boarded a boat by appointment "
"with nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized them,"

#. VAR: nāvāya → ekanāvāya (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.4"
msgid ""
"“yatheva mayaṃ sapajāpatikā nāvāya kīḷāma, evamevime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā "
"bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya nāvāya kīḷantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Just as we amuse ourselves on boats with our wives, so these Sakyan "
"ascetics make appointments with nuns and then amuse themselves on boats.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="610"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.5"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.8"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ "
"abhiruhissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six board boats by appointments with "
"nuns?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.9"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ "
"abhiruhathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.12"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ "
"abhiruhissatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you board boats by appointments with nuns?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a> 
#. <span class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="611"></a> 
#. VAR: ekaṃ nāvaṃ → ekanāvaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.15"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruheyya, "
"uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā adhogāminiṃ vā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk boards a boat by appointment with a nun, either to go upstream or "
"downstream, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="612"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.65"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.28.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="613"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū ca bhikkhuniyo ca sāketā sāvatthiṃ "
"addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti."
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards a number of monks and nuns were traveling from Sāketa to "
"Sāvatthī."

#. VAR: taritabbā → uttaritabbā (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "Antarāmagge nadī taritabbā hoti."
msgstr "On the way they had to cross a river,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and the nuns said to the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "“mayampi ayyehi saddhiṃ uttarissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“We’ll cross with you.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.293"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.5"
msgid ""
"“Na, bhaginī, kappati bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhituṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“Sisters, it’s not allowable for us to board a boat by appointment with a "
"nun."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "tumhe vā paṭhamaṃ uttaratha mayaṃ vā uttarissāmā”ti."
msgstr "You should cross first, or we will.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "“Ayyā, bhante, aggapurisā."
msgstr "“Venerables, you have the highest status."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "Ayyāva paṭhamaṃ uttarantū”ti."
msgstr "Please go first.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.9"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ pacchā uttarantīnaṃ corā acchindiṃsu ca "
"dūsesuñca."
msgstr ""
"But because the nuns crossed afterwards, they were robbed and raped by "
"bandits."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"When they arrived at Sāvatthī they told the nuns there what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The nuns then told the monks,"

#. <a class="wt-pa" id="614"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "who in turn told the Master."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.13"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.14"
msgid ""
"“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tiriyaṃ taraṇāya bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ "
"nāvaṃ abhiruhituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow you to board a boat by appointment with a nun if it’s for "
"the purpose of crossing."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "”And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.15a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="615"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: uddhaṅgāminiṃ → uddhagāminiṃ (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: tiriyaṃ taraṇāya → tiri­yantara­ṇāya (s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: ekaṃ nāvaṃ → ekanāvaṃ (s1-3)
#. VAR: abhiruheyya → abhirūheyya (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.16"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruheyya "
"uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā adhogāminiṃ vā, aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk boards a boat by appointment with a nun, either to go upstream or "
"downstream, unless it is for the purpose of crossing, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "(<em>28</em>:<strong>77</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.28.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.28.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="616"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… he monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through "
"a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="617"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "A nun:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.7"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "she has been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="618"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.8"
msgid "Saddhinti"
msgstr "With:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.9"
msgid "ekato."
msgstr "together."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="619"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.10"
msgid "Saṃvidhāyāti"
msgstr "By appointment:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.11"
msgid ""
"“abhiruhāma, bhagini, abhiruhāmāyya; abhiruhāmāyya, abhiruhāma, bhagini; "
"ajja vā hiyyo vā pare vā abhiruhāmā”ti saṃvidahati āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"if he makes an appointment like this: he says, “Let’s board, Sister,” and "
"she replies, “Yes, let’s board, Venerable;” or she says, “Lets’s board, "
"Venerable,” and he replies, “Yes, let’s board, Sister;” or he says, “Let’s "
"board today/tomorrow/the day after tomorrow,” then he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

#. </span>
#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="620"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.12"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyā abhiruḷhe bhikkhu abhiruhati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If the monk boards when the nun has already boarded, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.13"
msgid "Bhikkhumhi abhiruḷhe bhikkhunī abhiruhati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If the nun boards when the monks has already boarded, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.14"
msgid "Ubho vā abhiruhanti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If they both board together, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="621"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.15"
msgid "Uddhaṅgāmininti"
msgstr "To go upstream:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.16"
msgid "ujjavanikāya."
msgstr "for the purpose of going against the stream."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.294"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="622"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.17"
msgid "Adhogāmininti"
msgstr "To go downstream:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"><a class="wt-pa" id="623"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.18"
msgid "ojavanikāya."
msgstr "for the purpose of going with the stream."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.19"
msgid "Aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāyāti"
msgstr "Unless it is for the purpose of crossing:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.20"
msgid "ṭhapetvā tiriyaṃ taraṇaṃ."
msgstr "except to go across."

#. </span>
#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="624"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.21"
msgid "Kukkuṭasampāte gāme, gāmantare gāmantare āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"When the villages are a chicken’s flight apart, then for every village "
"interval he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. Half a <i lang="pli">yojana</i>. The length of a <i lang="pli">yojana</i> is uncertain, and perhaps it never was a precise distance. But a reasonable estimate is 8 miles or just under 13 kilometers (see ACMC, p.16). Thus half a <i lang="pli">yojana</i> is just over 6 km.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.1.22"
msgid "Agāmake araññe, aḍḍhayojane aḍḍhayojane āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is in an uninhabited area, in the wilderness, then for every six "
"kilometers he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.66"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.28.3.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="625"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.2.1"
msgid ""
"Saṃvidahite saṃvidahitasaññī ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhati uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā "
"adhogāminiṃ vā, aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāya, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If there is an appointment, and he perceives that there is, and he boards a "
"boat with a nun, either to go upstream or downstream, unless it is for the "
"purpose of crossing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.2.2"
msgid ""
"Saṃvidahite vematiko ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhati uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā adhogāminiṃ vā, "
"aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāya, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If there is an appointment, but he is unsure if there is, and he boards a "
"boat with a nun, either to go upstream or downstream, unless it is for the "
"purpose of crossing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.2.3"
msgid ""
"Saṃvidahite asaṃvidahitasaññī ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhati uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā "
"adhogāminiṃ vā, aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāya, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If there is an appointment, but he perceives that there is not, and he "
"boards a boat with a nun, either to go upstream or downstream, unless it is "
"for the purpose of crossing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="626"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.2.4"
msgid "Bhikkhu saṃvidahati, bhikkhunī na saṃvidahati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the monk makes an appointment, but the nun does not express her "
"agreement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.2.5"
msgid "Asaṃvidahite saṃvidahitasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If there is no appointment, but he perceives that there is, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.2.6"
msgid "Asaṃvidahite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If there is no appointment, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.2.7"
msgid "Asaṃvidahite, asaṃvidahitasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If there is no appointment, and he perceives that there is not, there is no "
"offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.28.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="627"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.3.2"
msgid "tiriyaṃ taraṇāya,"
msgstr "if it is for the purpose of crossing;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.3.3"
msgid "asaṃvidahitvā abhiruhanti,"
msgstr "if he boards without an appointment;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.3.4"
msgid "bhikkhunī saṃvidahati, bhikkhu na saṃvidahati,"
msgstr ""
"if the nun has made an appointment, but he has not expressed his agreement;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.3.5"
msgid "visaṅketena abhiruhanti,"
msgstr "if they board, but not according to the appointment;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.3.6"
msgid "āpadāsu,"
msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.3.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.3.8"
msgid "ādikammissāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="628"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:pts-cs3.3.9"
msgid "Nāvābhiruhanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The eighth rule, the training rule on boarding boats, is finished."

